Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g}(halved lengthways, then cut into thirds widthways).

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once boiled, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack} to the pan and season. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the rigatoni has been cooking for about ~{8%minutes}, add the Tenderstem® to the same pan and bring back to the boil.

Cook with the pasta for the last ~{3-4%minutes} of cooking time.

Once cooked, drain the pasta and broccoli in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the tomato sauce has thickened, add the @Butter{20%g} and @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan, a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the cooked pasta, broccoli, @Peas{120%g} and three quarters of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} into the sauce. Heat through until the peas are piping hot, ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the Cajun spiced tomato pasta out between your serving bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish.

Enjoy!